The Senators of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) will be meeting with the Mai Mala Buni-led Caretaker Extraordinary Convention Committee of the party at 2 pm on Tuesday. The deputy president of the senate, Ovie Omo-Agege, made the announcement at the start of plenary on Tuesday. Omo-Agege conveyed notice of the meeting in a latter addressed to the Senate President, Ahmad Lawan, and signed by the Senate Leader, Yahaya Abdullahi. The Senate president in the letter said the meeting would avail the Buni-led committee to brief the lawmakers on the forthcoming convention slated for March 26, 2022. He further disclosed that the former governor of Zamfara State and chairman of the Nigeria Governors Forum, Hon. Abdul’aziz Yari, would also address the caucus. Meanwhile, Presidential Aspirant of the People’s Democratic Party, Senator Bukola Saraki would also meet today with PDP Senators. Saraki was the president of the 8th Senate between 2015 and 2019. The notice of meeting between Saraki and members of the Senate PDP caucus was contained in a latter signed by the minority leader, Enyinnaya Abaribe. The letter was also read by the Deputy Senate President, Omo-Agege, who presided over plenary on Tuesday. The time of the meeting is slated for 7pm, Tuesday, March 22, 2022. 